original: Sleeping Giant Inn
string: 沉睡巨人旅店

original: Oh, er... sorry.
string: 呃，抱歉。

original: Hehe! Excuse me.
string: 呵呵！打扰一下

original: Did you hear that? You certainly weren't meant to.
string: 你听到那个了吗？你肯定不该听到这个。

original: Please excuse me. My stomach is a little off.
string: 请原谅，我的胃有点不舒服。

original: Oh! Excuse me.
string: 哦！打扰了。

original: More cheese for the Greybeards?!
string: 给灰胡子们更多的奶酪吗？！

original: Oh my. Sorry.
string: 哦，抱歉。

original: Er - whoops. I beg your pardon.
string: 呃——哎呀。请原谅。

original: I grace you with my once-noble gases!
string: 我赐予你我的稀有气体（屁）！

original: Oh, something just escaped from my buttocks.
string: 哦，有东西从我屁股里跑出来了。

original: Ha! That was funny!
string: 哈！真有趣！

original: I bet you didn't see that coming!
string: 我打赌你没想到会发生这样的事！

original: Oh, excuse me.
string: 哦，不好意思。

original: Whoops. Sorry.
string: 哎呀。对不起。

original: Oh come on, that's just wrong.
string: 哦，得了吧，那完全不对。

original: I am not 'impressed'. Impressed? Get it?
string: 我并不“印象深刻”。印象深刻？懂了吗？

original: I think I might throw up.
string: 我想我可能要吐了。

original: Oh my word. That's one of the worst smells I've ever heard. Er - smelled.
string: 天哪。那是我闻过的最难闻的气味之一。呃——是闻过的。

original: The good thing about having a skill like mine is you can blame someone else. It was me! I farted!
string: 像我这样的本事的好处就是可以把责任推给别人。是我！我放了个屁！

original: Oh please. You've done worse.
string: 哦，得了吧。你以前做过更糟糕的事。

original: Well, it's not like I can exactly afford good quality food, is it?
string: 好吧，我也买不起精美的食物，不是吗？

original: I didn't think it was that bad.
string: 我觉得它没有那么糟糕。

original: All this fuss over a little gas? Really?
string: 这点小屁就值得这么大惊小怪？真的？

original: I broke wind. The end.
string: 我放了个响屁。完事了。

original: I'm not going to lie. I honestly thought that would be silent.
string: 我不打算撒谎。说实话，我本以为那会是无声的。

original: Hey, what are you looking at? That wasn't me. It was it was - that guard. Yeah that one, over there.
string: 嘿，你在看什么？那不是我。是那个——那个守卫。对，就是那边那个。

original: What?!
string: 什麼？！

original: I blame it all on Odar's cooking.
string: 我把这一切都归咎于奥达尔的厨艺。

original: I bet bards will write songs about that one.
string: 我打赌，吟游诗人会为此写歌。

original: I'd say sorry, but I'm not.
string: 我本想说对不起，但我没有。

original: Don't look at me. It's the mead, I swear it.
string: 别看我，我发誓，是蜂蜜酒的原因。

original: Oh, that came out worse than I thought.
string: 哦，结果比我想象的还要糟糕。

original: Really? That's not very polite.
string: 真的吗？那不太礼貌。

original: Do you absolutely have to do that in front of me?
string: 你非得当着我的面做那件事吗？

original: What in the world was that?
string: 这到底是怎么回事？

original: Don't be so disgusting.
string: 别这么恶心。

original: Oh come on. That's awful, even by your standards.
string: 哦，得了吧。即使按照你的标准，那也太糟糕了。

original: W-what is... that... smell?
string: 那……那是什么……味道？

original: That's not very well mannered, is it now?
string: 这不太礼貌，是吧？

original: Do you mind?
string: 你介意吗？

original: I feel like it's tickling the inside of my nose.
string: 我感觉好像有东西在挠我的鼻子里。

original: Do you think that's funny? It's not.
string: 你觉得这很有趣吗？其实并不。

original: Do you mind? That's just bad manners!
string: 你介意吗？那太没礼貌了！

original: Hey! Don't do that, it's horrible.
string: 嘿！别那么做，太可怕了。

original: How do Khajiit end disagreements? They hiss and make up.
string: 卡吉特怎么结束争执？他们嘶嘶作态然后和好。

original: I put on a show for some ghosts once. I got booed off the stage.
string: 我曾经为一些幽灵表演。我被喝了倒彩轰下了台。

original: Why don't skeletons fight each other? They don't have the guts!
string: 为什么骷髅不互相打架？因为他们没有胆！

original: I went to High Hrothgar last week. I just wanted to know what all the 'Fus' was about.
string: 上周我去过高吼峰。我只是想弄清楚"Fus"是什么回事。

original: What does a cow say if you set its tail on fire? Mooo!
string: 你把牛的尾巴点着它会说什么？哞——！

original: A wizard once asked me to proofread one of his scrolls. I guess you could say it was a spell check.
string: 一位法师曾让我校对他的卷轴。我想你可以说那是在进行拼写检查。

original: What kind of magic makes people sad? Cryomancy.
string: 哪种魔法会让人感到悲伤？冰系占卜术。

original: Why did the Khajiit become a guard? Because he was interested in claw enforcement.
string: 为什么卡吉特会成为一名守卫？因为他热衷于执行爪法。

original: A Khajiit walks into a tavern and says 'Give me a mug of your... best... ale'. The innkeeper says, what's with the long paws?
string: 一只猫人走进酒馆，说道：“给我来一杯你们……最好的……麦芽酒。”店主问道：“你的爪子怎么这么长？”？

original: Why don't mudcrabs give to charity? Because they're shellfish.
string: 为什么泥沼蟹不慈善？因为它们很自私。

original: What do you call a parade of rabbits hopping backwards? A receding hare-line.
string: 你怎么称呼一队倒着跳的兔子？后退的发际线。

original: I visited a Redguard vegetable stall the other day. They had curved gourds. Curved. Gourds.
string: 前几天我去了一个红卫人的蔬菜摊。他们有弯的葫芦。弯的。葫芦。

original: What's the first thing wizards do in the morning? They wake up.
string: 巫师早上第一件事做什么？他们醒来。

original: What kind of dog tells the time? A watch dog.
string: 什么狗能报时？看门狗。

original: I slept like a log last night. I woke up in a fireplace.
string: 我昨晚睡得像个木柴。醒来时却在壁炉里。

original: A horse walks into a tavern. The innkeeper says 'why the long face?'
string: 一匹马走进酒馆。店主说：“怎么拉长着脸？”

original: A moth priest walks into a bar.  And a chair.  And a table.
string: 一位飞蛾祭司走进酒吧。还有一把椅子。还有一张桌子。

original: What do you call a Thane of Solitude that speaks two languages? Bry-lingual!
string: 你会怎么称呼一个会说两种语言的孤独领主呢？双语领主！

original: What do you get from a pampered cow? Spoiled milk.
string: 娇生惯养的牛产什么？被宠坏的罐装奶。

original: A bard threatened to attack me with the neck of his lute. I said 'Is that a fret?'
string: 一个吟游诗人威胁要用他的鲁特琴琴颈攻击我。我说“那是琴品吗？”

original: What's orange and sounds like a parrot? A carrot.
string: 什么东西是橙色的，听起来像鹦鹉？答案是胡萝卜。

original: What does a dog say when you tell it a joke? Woof.
string: 你讲笑话时狗会说什么？汪！

original: What letter in the alphabet holds the most amount of water? C.
string: 字母表里哪个字母装的水最多？C。

original: What do you call a hat for your leg? A kneecap.
string: 你管腿上的帽子叫什么？膝盖帽。

original: Well that was pretty obvious. I won.
string: 那太明显了。我赢了。

original: Well, clearly they liked me more.
string: 好吧，显然他们更喜欢我。

original: That's settled that. You're not funny. I am.
string: 那就这么定了。你不好笑，我才是。

original: Well, obviously I won that round.
string: 嗯，显然我赢了那一局。

original: The audience definitely laughed more at my jokes.
string: 我的笑话确实让观众笑得更欢。

original: Happy now? I claim victory.
string: 现在高兴了吧？我宣布获胜。

original: Well that went well - for me, obviously.
string: 嗯，对我来说，显然，事情进展得很顺利。

original: I did enjoy wiping the floor with you Ongbarn. Better luck next time, eh?
string: 确实很享受和翁邦把你打得落花流水。下次好运，对吧？

original: Yeah, even when I use your voice, I'm funnier than the real you.
string: 是啊，就算我用你的声音，我也比真正的你更有趣。

original: That wasn't a challenge at all. I'm the clear winner.
string: 那根本不是挑战。我显然是赢家。

original: My name is Lydia and I would definitely say Aperic is funnier than Ongbarn.
string: 我叫莉迪亚，我肯定会说阿佩里克比翁邦有趣。

original: Yes. The jester mortal named Aperic is funnier than the one called Ongbarn. Far funnier, in fact.
string: 是的。那个名叫阿佩里克的凡人小丑比那个叫翁巴恩的小丑更有趣。事实上，有趣得多。

original: Come on lad. Just accept that I'm funnier than you.
string: 得了吧，小伙子。你就承认我比你更有趣吧。

original: Proper funny me. Not pretend funny like you, you ponce.
string: 我才是真正的好笑，不像你这种假笑，你这家伙。

original: That wasn't funny at all.
string: 这一点也不好笑。

original: Come on. That was weak.
string: 得了吧。那也太弱了吧。

original: Heard it before.
string: 以前听过。

original: Pathetic.
string: 可悲。

original: Call that a joke?
string: 这算是个笑话吗？

original: Not funny in the slightest.
string: 一点也不好笑。

original: Huh?
string: 嗯？

original: What? I don't even get it.
string: 什么？我甚至都没明白。

original: Boring!
string: 无聊！

original: Not funny.
string: 不好笑。

original: Oh don't be silly.
string: 哦，别傻了。

original: Uh - no!
string: 哦 - 不!

original: Uh - no!
string: 哦 - 不!

original: Seriously?
string: 真的吗？

original: People really laugh at this stuff?
string: 人们真的会为这些东西发笑吗？

original: That's not funny.
string: 这不好笑。

original: You're a failure.
string: 你是个失败者。

original: That one was rubbish.
string: 那部电影真烂。

original: Huh?
string: 嗯？

original: I'm Ongbarn. I'm dumb!
string: 我是翁邦。我是笨蛋！

original: I'm just seriously confused right now.
string: 我现在真的非常困惑。

original: What's going on?
string: 發生什麼事了？

original: I-I, don't get what's happening.
string: 我，我，不明白发生了什么。

original: These so-called jesters eh?
string: 这些所谓的弄臣，是吧？

original: I won that, you agree, right?
string: 我赢了，你同意吧？

original: I'll be glad to see the back of that fool.
string: 我很高兴能摆脱那个傻瓜。

original: That Aperic is a weird one, right?
string: 那阿佩里克真是个古怪的人，对吧？

original: You know I'm funnier than Gorthe right? Right?!
string: 你知道我比戈斯更有趣，对吧？正确的

original: A female jester? Bah, what's that about?
string: 女小丑？呸，这算怎么回事？

original: What in Oblivion just happened?
string: 湮灭里到底发生了什么？

original: Oh. It's you.
string: 哦，是你。

original: Wait? Is that supposed to be me?
string: 等等？那应该是我吗？

original: Are you impersonating me?
string: 你在冒充我吗？

original: What did you say?
string: 你说了什么呢？

original: What was that?
string: 那是什麼？

original: Say that again! I dare you!
string: 再说一遍！我赌你敢！

original: That doesn't sound like me at all.
string: 那听起来完全不像我。

original: Stop it. You're messing with my head.
string: 别这样。你把我弄糊涂了。

original: Oh come on. I'm just as funny as you, if not funnier.
string: 哦，得了吧。我跟你一样有趣，甚至可能更有趣。

original: Really? People seem to laugh at my jokes more than yours.
string: 真的吗？人们似乎对我的笑话比对你的笑话笑得更厉害。

original: I don't think so. My jokes are more original than yours.
string: 我不这么认为。我的笑话比你的更有创意。

original: Well I guess there's only one way to find out.
string: 好吧，我想只有一个办法能知道了。

original: We'll see about that. Let's find out shall we?
string: 我们拭目以待。让我们来一探究竟，好吗？

original: How about we prove who's funnier then? Or are you scared?
string: 要不我们比一比，看谁更风趣？还是你害怕了？

original: A competition. We take turns telling jokes and see who gets more laughs.
string: 比赛。我们轮流讲笑话，看谁得到的笑声更多。

original: We each tell our jokes and let the audience decide.
string: 我们各自讲笑话，然后让观众来决定。

original: We both deliver our best jokes and see who laughs the hardest.
string: 我们各自讲出自己最好的笑话，然后看看谁让人笑得最厉害。

original: What's the difference between a pirate and a fruit farmer? One buries his treasure, the other treasures his berries.
string: 海盗和果农有什么区别？一个埋藏财宝，一个珍惜浆果。

original: Why shouldn't pigs drive carriages? Because they'll hog the road.
string: 为什么猪不该驾驶马车？因为它们会霸占整条路。

original: What do you call an elf that is a member of the Dark Brotherhood? A murdermer.
string: 你如何称呼一个属于黑暗兄弟会的精灵？杀人犯。

original: Why do shy people like to live in Haafingar? Because they like Solitude.
string: 为什么害羞的人喜欢住在哈芬加尔？因为他们喜欢独处。

original: What's the weather like on Solstheim? Yesterday - sunny. Today - raining. Tomorrow wind.
string: 索尔斯特海姆的天气怎么样？昨天是晴天。今天下雨。明天有风。

original: What crime is it when a Spriggan kills another Spriggan? Tree-son.
string: 树精杀死另一个树精算什么罪？树精叛国罪。

original: A sweetroll walks into a tavern and asks for a pint of ale. The innkeeper says 'sorry, we don't serve food here'.
string: 一个甜卷走进酒馆要一品脱麦芽酒。店主说‘对不起，我们这里不供应食物’。

original: Where in Skyrim would you take your footwear to get repaired? The Sole Cairn.
string: 在天际中，你会去哪里修理鞋子呢？去鞋匠凯恩那里。

original: Who can enter the Emperor's chamber? Nobody Septim.
string: 谁可以进入皇帝的寝宫？只有西吉姆。

original: What do the Daedra make their clothes out of? Mala-cloth.
string: 戴达拉族用什么材料制作衣服？玛拉布。

original: When do ducks wake up? At the quack of dawn.
string: 鸭子什么时候醒来？破晓时分。

original: I asked a guard if he knew the alphabet. He said no, but as I was walking away, the guard said 'wait! I know U'.
string: 我问一个守卫是否认识字母表。他说不认识，但当我走开时，守卫说：‘等等！我认识你！’

original: I got kicked out of the college in Solitude. You might say I was dis-bard.
string: 我被孤独学院开除了。你也可以说我被吊销了执照。

original: Why do Khajiit wear armor? Fur protection of course.
string: 为什么卡吉特人要戴盔甲？当然是为了保护他们的毛皮。

original: What type of beer do they drink in Dawnstar? Pale ale.
string: 在晨星，他们喝什么类型的啤酒？淡色艾尔啤酒。

original: I - uh - what you did? Isn't that - uh cheating?
string: 我——呃——你刚才做了什么？这不是作弊吗？

original: Are you kidding? They clearly liked me better?
string: 你在开玩笑吗？他们明明更喜欢我？

original: Oh come on. I won. Is there something wrong with your ears?
string: 哦，得了吧。我赢了。你的耳朵有问题吗？

original: You're unbelievable. I give up.
string: 你真是难以置信。我放弃了。

original: Oh, hello Ongbarn.
string: 哦，你好，翁邦。

original: Yes of course it's me. Who else would it be?
string: 当然是我了。还会是谁呢？

original: Yep, it's me alright.
string: 没错，就是我。

original: Well that's not much of a hello, is it?
string: 好吧，这算不上是打招呼，是吧？

original: Ongbarn! My nemesis!
string: 哦，翁邦！我的克星！

original: Oh, fancy running into you here.
string: 哦，真没想到在这儿碰到你。

original: Well if it isn't the famous Ongbarn.
string: 哎呀，这不是大名鼎鼎的翁邦吗。

original: Oh look what the cat dragged in.
string: 哦，看看那只猫拖来了什么。

original: Still not funny I see.
string: 我看还是不好笑。

original: The man with the worst jokes in Skyrim.
string: 天际省讲笑话最烂的人。

original: Still telling those things you dare call 'jokes' eh?
string: 还在讲那些你所谓的“笑话”吗？

original: So Ongbarn, still struggling to make people laugh I take it?
string: 所以，翁邦，我看你还在努力逗人笑呢？

original: My name is Ongbarn, and I'm not funny.
string: 我叫翁邦，我并不幽默。

original: Oh I tell really bad jokes and people laugh just to be polite.
string: 哦，我讲的笑话真的很糟糕，人们只是出于礼貌才笑。

original: The unfunniest man in Skyrim.
string: 天际大陆上最无趣的人。

original: The teller of pathetic jokes.
string: 讲低俗笑话的人。

original: Oh come on now, you're not even a proper jester, you're just not funny.
string: 哦，得了吧，你甚至算不上一个合格的逗乐者，你根本就不搞笑。

original: Here's the facts. I make people laugh. You don't.
string: 事实就是，我能逗人笑，而你不能。

original: Well, at the risk of repeating myself, you're not very funny are you?
string: 好吧，冒着重复的风险，你其实并不怎么有趣，是吧？

original: I'm pretty sure you know what I said, but to be clear, I insulted your joke telling abilities.
string: 我敢肯定你知道我说了什么，但我要明确一点，我侮辱了你的讲笑话能力。

original: Yes, I was doing your voice, that's exactly what you sound like. I'm Ongbarn and I sound like a whiny little skeever.
string: 是的，我在模仿你的声音，你听起来就是这样。我是翁邦，我听起来就像一只爱抱怨的小老鼠。

original: Ha! This never gets old.
string: 哈！这永远都不过时。

original: You heard me well enough.
string: 你听得够清楚了。

original: Are you deaf, as well as bland?
string: 你是聋子，还这么无趣吗？

original: No, no, no. I'm so much funnier than you, it's not even funny.
string: 不不不。我比你有趣多了，根本不是一个级别。

original: I always get more of a laugh than you do.
string: 我总是比你更引人发笑。

original: Now 'that' was funny. But really? I'm much funnier than you are.
string: 现在，那确实很有趣。但说真的？我比你有趣多了。

original: You can't seriously believe that you're funnier than me? You're not even funnier than Hurbjorf in Winterhold, and he's seriously not funny.
string: 你不会真的以为你比我更有趣吧？你甚至还不如冬堡的赫布约夫有趣，而他真的不搞笑。

original: I'm funnier than you, even when I am you.
string: 即使我变成你，我也比你更有趣。

original: Silly little man. You're not funny at all.
string: 愚蠢的小个子。你一点也不好笑。

original: I don't think so.
string: 我不這麼認為。

original: You really think you're funny?
string: 你真的觉得自己很幽默吗？

original: This should be interesting. Go on.
string: 这应该会很有趣。继续吧。

original: Well, what do you have in mind?
string: 那么，你有什么想法吗？

original: I'm interested in proving it, what's the deal?
string: 我对证明这件事很感兴趣，到底是怎么回事？

original: Oh I bet this is going to be fun.
string: 哦，我打赌这会很有趣。

original: Spit it out then.
string: 那就说出来吧。

original: Let's hear this cunning plan of yours then.
string: 那么，让我们听听你那个狡猾的计划吧。

original: What are you suggesting?
string: 你有什么建议？

original: Go on. I'm listening.
string: 繼續。我在聽。

original: Very well. I accept your challenge.
string: 很好。我接受你的挑战。

original: Let's do it then. I will prove I'm funnier.
string: 那就这么办吧。我会证明我比他更有趣。

original: Let the joke battle commence. You can go first.
string: 笑话大战开始吧。你先来。

original: Oh this is a nice idea, I'll wipe the floor with you.
string: 哦，这是个好主意，我会把你打得满地找牙。

original: I accept. Let's go.
string: 我接受。我们走吧。

original: Bring it on then. But you just know I'll be imitating you.
string: 那就来吧。但你肯定知道，我会模仿你的。

original: You're on. You go first.
string: 你上吧。你先来。

original: Let's go then. You can start it off.
string: 那么开始吧。你可以先开始。

original: What do you call a pile of cats? A meow-ntain.
string: 你怎么称呼一堆猫？喵山。

original: Where would you find a mudcrab with no legs? Where you left it.
string: 你能在哪儿找到一条没有腿的泥沼蟹？在你把它丢弃的地方。

original: I've got a dog you know. It's very good at smithing. If you kick it, it makes a bolt for the door.
string: 你知道的，我养了一只狗。它非常擅长打铁。如果你踢它，它会迅速逃向门口。

original: Where do vampires keep their money? In a blood bank.
string: 吸血鬼把钱存在哪里？血液银行。

original: What's a cat's favorite color? Purr-ple.
string: 猫最喜欢什么颜色？喵紫色。

original: What do Mjoll the Lioness and Grelod the Kind have in common? They both have the same middle name.
string: 母狮姆乔尔和仁慈的格雷洛德有什么共同之处？他们俩的中间名相同。

original: Why did the thieves Guild split up? There was a Rift-en the ranks.
string: 盗贼公会为何分裂？因为他们呆在裂谷。

original: What do the true sons and daughters of Skyrim wear when it rains? A Storm cloak!
string: 天际真正的儿女下雨天穿什么？风暴斗篷！

original: What do you call a fish with no eye? A fsh.
string: 你怎么称呼一条没有眼睛的鱼？福石。

original: An orc walks into a bar. The bar breaks.
string: 一个兽人走进酒吧。酒吧崩塌了。

original: What is the most common crime for blacksmiths? Forgery.
string: 铁匠最常见的犯罪是什么？伪造。

original: Why did the farmer bury his money in a field. He wanted to make his soil rich.
string: 为什么农民要把钱埋在田里呢？他想让他的土地变得肥沃。
